      <title outputclass="H4ForH3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">3.103-2</ph> Evaluating
the certification.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d86e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin"
                otherprops="abcRunin"
                outputclass="H5_abcRunin"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d88e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> 
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Evaluation
guidelines</i>.</p>
               <ol id="d86e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123FL" outputclass="H6_123FL" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d88e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> None of the following, in and
of itself, constitutes “disclosure” as it is used in <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 3.103-2 by—
a.  Removing from paragraph (a)(1) introductory text “subparagraph (a)(2)” and adding “paragraph (a)(2)” in its place;
?>paragraph <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>(a)(2)</ph> of
the Certificate of Independent Price Determination (hereafter, the
certificate):</p>
                     <ol id="d86e33" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d88e43" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> The fact
that a firm has published price lists, rates, or tariffs covering
items being acquired by the Government.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d88e52" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> The fact
that a firm has informed prospective customers of proposed or pending
publication of new or revised price lists for items being acquired
by the Government.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d88e61" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> The fact
that a firm has sold the same items to commercial customers at the
same prices being offered to the Government.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d88e72" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> For the purpose of <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] b.  Removing from paragraph (a)(2) introductory text “subparagraph (b)(2)” and adding “paragraph (b)(2)” in its place;?>paragraph <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>(b)(2)</ph> of
the certificate, an individual may use a blanket authorization to
act as an agent for the person(s) responsible for determining the
offered prices if-</p>
                     <ol id="d86e72" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d88e88" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> The proposed
contract to which the certificate applies is clearly within the
scope of the authorization; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d88e97" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> The person
giving the authorization is the person within the offeror’s organization
who is responsible for determining the prices being offered at the
time the certification is made in the particular offer.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d88e108" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> If an offer is submitted jointly
by two or more concerns, the certification provided by the representative
of each concern applies only to the activities of that concern.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin"
                otherprops="abcRunin"
                outputclass="H5_abcRunin"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d88e119" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Rejection
of offers suspected of being collusive.</p>
               <ol id="d86e113" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123FL" outputclass="H6_123FL" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d88e129" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>  If the offeror deleted or <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph ">modified <?FM MARKER [Why] c.  Removing from paragraph (b)(1) “modified subparagraph (a)(1)” and adding “modified paragraph (a)(1)” in its place;?>paragraph <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>(a)(1)</ph> or
(a)(3) or paragraph (b) of the certificate, the contracting officer
shall reject the offeror’s bid or proposal.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d88e145" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> If the offeror deleted or <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph ">modified <?FM MARKER [Why] d.  Removing from paragraph (b)(2) “modified subparagraph (a)(2)” and adding “modified paragraph (a)(2)” in its place;?>paragraph <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>(a)(2)</ph> of
the certificate, the offeror must have furnished with its offer a
signed statement of the circumstances of the disclosure of prices
contained in the bid or proposal. The chief of the contracting office
shall review the altered certificate and the statement and shall
determine, in writing, whether the disclosure was made for the purpose
or had the effect of restricting competition. If the determination
is positive, the bid or proposal shall be rejected; if it is negative,
the bid or proposal shall be considered for award.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d88e161" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Whenever an offer is rejected <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph ">under <?FM MARKER [Why] e.  Removing from paragraph (b)(3) “under subparagraph (1) or (2) above” and adding “under paragraph (b)(1) or (b)(2) of this section” in its place; and?>paragraph <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>(b)(1)
or (b)(2)</ph> of this section, or the certificate is suspected
of being false, the contracting officer shall report the situation
to the Attorney General in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1124523.dita#i1124523"
                              base="i1124523"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.303</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d88e180" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> The determination made <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph ">under <?FM MARKER [Why] f.  Removing from paragraph (b)(4) “under subparagraph (2)” and adding “under paragraph (2)” in its place.?>paragraph <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments
?>(b)(2)</ph> of
this section shall not prevent or inhibit the prosecution of any criminal
or civil actions involving the occurrences or transactions to which
the certificate relates.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
